s. We suggest that future detector design should consider reducing\nlightning coupling by, for example, reducing the lightning-induced beam tube\ncurrents that pass through sensitive magnetic coupling regions in current\ndetectors. We also suggest that the diurnal and seasonal variation in lightning\nactivity may be useful in discriminating between detector correlations that are\nproduced by gravitational waves and those produced by lightning.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Sep 2022 08:05:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-25"}
