e \\Upsilon=0. Thus, if\n\\varphi_{in}^{(min)}\\leq \\varphi_{in}<\\varphi_0 and\n\\rho_{kin}^{(in)}>\\rho_{grad}^{(in)}, then there was an inflationary stage in\nthe history of our Universe and the congruence of timelike geodesics cannot be\nextended to the past beyond the hypersurface \\Upsilon=0.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Sep 2022 11:43:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 26 Sep 2022 04:26:52 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 11 Oct 2022 14:51:54 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 10 Apr 2023 17:18:21 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Tue, 2 May 2023 03:58:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-10"}
